 beyond local persistence readback.","test_description":"Execute chat flow against a real local test DB, force a regeneration path, then read back stored records and assert all turns/regenerations exist with correct linkage and timestamps.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.07,"Integration":0.8,"System":0.11,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the tone check triggers regeneration, the second response replaces the first — the customer never sees the rejected draft.","required_reality_check_level":"System","justification":"SYSTEM TRIAD trigger 3 applies: this is an externally visible side-effect guarantee ('customer never sees'). You must verify the real outward interface only exposes the regenerated response, not just internal function state. Integration with in-process assertions can miss real delivery/ordering behavior at the boundary. Rejection gate: Agentic/Workflow were considered and rejected because this behavior is about external exposure semantics; model-quality assertions are not required if trigger conditions are controlled.","test_description":"Run the service through its real delivery boundary (e.g., real HTTP/chat endpoint), induce regeneration, and assert the customer-visible response payload/stream contains only the second draft while the first remains internal-only.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.23,"System":0.68,"Agentic":0.06,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
